programme.title: M*A*S*H
programme.desc: A beloved, multi-Emmy-winning series about Army surgeons cutting up amid the Korean War. 'War is hell. So is TV,' said Larry Gelbart, who developed the series for TV from the 1970 Robert Altman film. ' 'M*A*S*H' and the medium,' Gelbart added, 'were made for each other.' For 11 years (10 in the Top 20), the show deftly blended sharp, thoughtful humor with moving scenes of dedicated, stressed doctors trying to save lives---while clinging to their own sanity---in a Mobile Army Surgical Hospital.

programme.title: Bonanza
programme.desc: Ben Cartwright and his three sons (by three wives) ride herd over the sprawling Ponderosa spread in 1860s Nevada in one of the most handsomely mounted and beloved series of all time. The first TV Western to be shown in color, it ran for 14 seasons; was the top-rated show for three of them (1964-65, '65-66 and '66-67); had a number of first-rank directors (including Robert Altman) work on some episodes; and inspired several 'Bonanza' TV-movies (none especially distinctive).

programme.title: Gunsmoke
programme.desc: This landmark adult Western centered on Marshal Matt Dillon of Dodge City. John Wayne turned down the lead, suggesting James Arness (who remained for its entire run). Originating on radio (with William Conrad as Dillon), it moved to TV in September 1955. Its popularity spawned a number of copycats, but none would enjoy the longevity (and few the consistent quality) of this classic.

programme.title: The Andy Griffith Show
programme.desc: Gentle humor and genuinely likable characters made Mayberry a beloved fixture on the TV landscape. A Top 10 hit throughout its eight-year run (it went out at No. 1), this low-key, down-home sitcom harkened back to a simpler time and place. Mayberry may be a state of mind, but the sunny optimism and simple virtues it represents have actually been set in stone--in a Raleigh, N.C., statue depicting Sheriff Andy Taylor and his son, Opie. '[The show's] central theme was love,' Griffith said.

programme.title: Everybody Loves Raymond
programme.desc: Ray Romano hit the sitcom stratosphere with this gem based on his stand-up routine. It's about a Long Island sportswriter and his intrusive parents, who live (in)conveniently across the street from him, his wife and their three children. Romano and costars Patricia Heaton, Doris Roberts, Peter Boyle and Brad Garrett were virtual Emmy-nomination machines and scored eight wins among them. Boyle alone, curiously, never took home the prize.

programme.title: Drumline

An offbeat and touching comedy-drama directed by Craig Gillespie and written by Nancy Oliver. Emily Mortimer, Paul Schneider.

programme.title: Risky Business
programme.desc: A teenager with a bright future turns his house into a brothel while his parents are away, falls for a prostitute and earns the wrath of Guido the Killer Pimp in this comedy highlighted by Tom Cruise's star-making performance.

programme.title: White Noise
programme.desc: Michael Keaton's haunting performance guides this spine-tingling thriller about an architect who becomes consumed with contacting his dead wife's spirit through electronic devices. Chandra West, Deborah Kara Unger, Ian McNeice, Sarah Strange.

programme.title: The Photograph
programme.desc: The estranged daughter of a famed photographer initiates a romantic relationship with an up-and-coming journalist who is working on a story about her late mother's life and artistic legacy after discovering an old photograph in a safe-deposit box.

programme.title: Mare of Easttown
programme.desc: Det. Mare Sheehan shoulders her chief's directive to revive an unsolved missing person's case amid increased community pressure. Later, while her loved ones celebrate her ex-husband Frank's engagement, Mare attends a celebration for her legendary high school basketball win and connects with Richard, a professor who's new in town. Series premiere.

programme.title: Mare of Easttown
programme.desc: Mare visits a grisly murder scene before informing the victim's enraged father. As a video from the night of the crime surfaces, Mare questions suspects in the case and gives an icy welcome to County Detective Colin Zabel, who's been called in to assist. Later, Mare bumps heads with locals and airs concerns about her grandson Drew in light of her late son's mental health struggles.

programme.title: Mare of Easttown

After lashing out at Helen about a possible custody fight over Drew, Mare receives some unprompted advice from Richard on how to move forward with Carrie. Later, Kenny and Mare face the consequences of their misguided attempts to protect their families.

programme.title: Doubt
programme.desc: Writer-director John Patrick Shanley adapts his Pulitzer Prize-winning play into an incendiary battle of wills involving a demagogic nun (Meryl Streep) who's convinced that the parish priest (Philip Seymour Hoffman) is engaged in sexual misconduct with a 12-year-old male student (Joseph Foster II) in their Bronx grade school. A top-notch ensemble cast is excellently aided by Amy Adams as a young nun and Viola Davis as the young boy's mother.

programme.title: Misery
programme.desc: Angry that he killed off her hero, a woman holds her favorite novelist hostage to make him write a new book the way she wants it.

programme.title: Ford v Ferrari
programme.desc: In the 1960s, Ferrari is an untouchable figure in racing. With Enzo Ferrari ardently chasing after excellence, the company is irrefutably the best there is. Ford's Henry Ford II wants in on the success, and so he journeys to Italy to propose a merger with the automobile giant. His plan, however, is met with ridicule. With a hurt ego, he enlists the help of car designer Carroll Shelby and driver Ken Miles to build a car that would defeat Ferrari at the 1966 24 Hours of Le Mans.

programme.title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
programme.sub-title: Last Week Tonight with John Oliver 219
programme.desc: COVID-19 vaccines and vaccine hesitancy; and U.S. government agencies on social media are discussed.

programme.title: Irresistible

But when the Republican National Committee discovers this strategy, they send in their best political strategist, Faith, who happens to be Gary's long-time nemesis in the political arena.

programme.title: The Family Man

He plays a rich, ruthless businessman who's shown the life he might have had by a guardian angel (Don Cheadle) who transforms him into a suburban working stiff with a wife (Tea Leoni), kids and minivan. Brett Ratner directed. Jeremy Piven, Saul Rubinek, Josef Sommer, Makenzie Vega.

programme.title: Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure
programme.desc: Two dim best friends who dream of being famous rock stars time-travel in order to bring ancient figures to modern times so that they can pass a history class and graduate. If they fail, one of them will be forced to join the military.

programme.title: In & Out
programme.desc: Kevin Kline's comic turn highlights this winning farce about a straitlaced teacher whose world is shattered when a former student refers to him as gay on TV. programme.title: The Watch
programme.desc: Four suburbanites stumble upon an alien invasion while volunteering as a neighborhood-watch group, and they fight to protect their block from evil extraterrestrials in this madcap sci-fi comedy.

programme.title: The New Mutants
programme.desc: When Illyana, Rahne, Sam, Danielle, and Roberto — five teenage mutants who are just discovering their superhuman abilities — are held inside an isolated hospital to be psychologically monitored, strange occurrences begin to happen. As events intensify, they find themselves embarking on a mission to escape the facility and save their lives, putting their newfound friendship and powers to the ultimate test.

programme.title: Shaun of the Dead
programme.desc: Yuks and yucks collide in this uproarious British comedy, a seamless blend of wit and horror. Simon Pegg stars as a beer-swilling slacker who tries to get his miserable life in order while repelling the zombies that have overrun London. Pegg also co-wrote the script with director Edgar Wright. Kate Ashfield, Nick Frost, Lucy Davis, Bill Nighy, Martin Freeman.

programme.title: Birds of Prey: And the Fantabulous Emancipation of One Harley Quinn (?)
programme.desc: After she begins to operate independently from the Joker, Harley Quinn teams up with Black Canary, Huntress, and Detective Renee Montoya to save a young street thief from a contract killing that has been initiated by Black Mask, a brutal and narcissistic Gotham City crime lord.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: In 1899 London, Amalia True and Penance Adair work to protect their kind from widespread, deepening antipathy, three years after an inexplicable event suddenly equipped them with extraordinary abilities. Meanwhile, police inspector Frank Mundi investigates a string of murders at the hands of a reportedly Touched and highly dangerous serial killer named Maladie. Series premiere.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city reels from Maladie's opera debut as Mundi takes a personal stake in tracking her down, and Amalia launches an investigation of her own. Meanwhile, the charitable Lavinia Bidlow seeks to destigmatize the Touched at a society event; Hugo Swann enlists Lavinia's younger brother Augie to help monetize his illicit enterprise; and a deranged doctor conducts a series of experiments.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: Penance creates an amplifier to spread Mary's hope-inspiring song across the city, but first, Mary must find her elusive voice. As danger mounts against her group, Amalia propositions an unlikely ally and sets out to expand the Orphanage's reach. Swann further entangles Augie and Mundi in his business affairs.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: While Mundi seeks justice, Amalia and her most trusted advisors make a list of potential enemies; Harriet, Primrose, and the other Orphans attempt to decipher a message; and later, Amalia exposes an unexpected threat.

programme.title: Man Up
programme.desc: In this delightful romantic-comedy Nancy, an unlucky-in-love thirtysomething, meets Jack, a heartbroken divorcé who has recently tried online dating and mistakes Nancy for his arranged blind date when they cross paths. Nancy plays along with the ruse, and the unlikely duo soon find themselves on a whirlwind journey neither of them expected.

programme.title: Hot Fuzz
programme.desc: Director-writer Edgar Wright, writer-star Simon Pegg and costar Nick Frost, the U.K. trio behind the frighteningly silly but bloody hilarious \"Shaun of the Dead,\" reunite for this smashingly entertaining cop-buddy joyride. Pegg is a big-city superofficer who gets teamed with Frost's small-town booby bobby to fight crime in the quaint old town of Sandford, where things are not as calm as they seem. Features cameos by Cate Blanchett, Timothy Dalton and director Peter Jackson.

programme.title: 40 Days and 40 Nights
programme.desc: Romantic comedy about a young man so frustrated by love that he decides to give up sex for Lent, a vow that leaves him scrambling for an explanation when he meets the girl of his dreams.

programme.title: Confessions of a Dangerous Mind
programme.desc: George Clooney made his directorial debut with this wry, tongue-in-cheek drama about Chuck Barris (Sam Rockwell), the game-show host from the '60s and '70s who claims that his flamboyant career was a cover for his double life...as a CIA assassin. Screenwriter Charlie Kaufman adapted Barris's \"unauthorized autobiography.\" Drew Barrymore, Julia Roberts, George Clooney, Maggie Gyllenhaal.

programme.title: Timeline
programme.desc: Richard Donner directed this thrilling adaptation of Michael Crichton's novel about a team of modern-day archaeological students trying to rescue their mentor (Billy Connolly) from 14th-century France. Paul Walker, Frances O'Connor, Gerard Butler, David Thewlis, Anna Friel, Neal McDonough, Michael Sheen, Lambert Wilson, Matt Craven, Ethan Embry.

programme.title: Rock of Ages
programme.desc: Brilliant adaptation of the off-Broadway musical about two dreamers who fall in love during the height of the hair-metal scene as they navigate the seedy world of drugs, mullets and stripping.

programme.title: Hero
programme.desc: Martial arts master Jet Li stars in this stylized action adventure from acclaimed director Zhang Yimou. The \"Rashomon\"-style epic centers on a swordsman who claims to have saved a ruthless Chinese emperor from a trio of assassins.

programme.title: He Got Game
programme.desc: Spike Lee's moving story centers on a killer (Denzel Washington) who is granted a temporary leave from prison to persuade his son (NBA star Ray Allen, in his big-screen debut), a talented young basketball player, to attend the governor's alma mater. Milla Jovovich, Rosario Dawson, Hill Harper.

programme.title: Fear
programme.desc: What begins as an innocent teenage romance turns to obsession when a charismatic but unbalanced young man sets his sights on a 16-year-old girl.

programme.title: Dim Sum Funeral
programme.desc: After their mother passes away, four estranged siblings return home to attend the traditional funeral she wanted.

programme.title: Sunshine Cleaning
programme.desc: A single mom struggling to make ends meet persuades her slacker sister to go into the crime-scene-cleanup business to make some quick cash. Amy Adams and Emily Blunt star in this quirky, well-acted dramedy from the producers of \"Little Miss Sunshine.\" Alan Arkin, Jason Spevack, Steve Zahn. Directed by Christine Jeffs.

programme.title: Dirty Dancing
programme.desc: An innocent teen vacationing with her upper-middle-class parents at an upscale resort in the 1960s Catskills gets a jolt of culture shock when she crushes on the hotel's slick, handsome dance instructor. The soundtrack yielded the Oscar-winning Best Song \"(I've Had the) Time of My Life.\".

programme.title: Pray, Obey, Kill
programme.desc: Anton and Martin seek to verify the source behind the anonymous texts, as former members reveal the mental and physical abuse they endured during the congregation's final days. Series finale.

programme.title: The Namesake
programme.desc: A Bengali family tries to acclimate to life in the U.S. in this poignant and bittersweet saga of cultures clashing across generations. Their teenage son (Kal Penn) does not embrace their Indian heritage until he visits Calcutta, where he gains an understanding of the importance of his family's past. Indian-born Mira Nair directed from a script by Sooni Taraporevala, who adapted Pulitzer Prize-winner Jhumpa Lahiri's novel. Bollywood superstar Tabu costars as Penn's old-world mother.

programme.title: Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy
programme.desc: In this riveting Cold War thriller set in 1970s England, a disgraced spy named George Smiley (Gary Oldman) is hired by his government to expose a double agent in British intelligence who is selling secrets to the Soviets.

programme.title: Our Brand Is Crisis
programme.desc: In this smart, satrical comedy, a female political consultant is hired to work on the campaign of a Bolivian presidential candidate who has fallen behind in the polls. She faces off against her rival, who is working on the opponent's campaign and is looking for every opportunity to antagonize her.

programme.title: Words and Pictures
programme.desc: In this delightfully witty comedy-drama, an English teacher challenges an art teacher to a contest to determine whether words or images are more powerful. As the student body are drawn into the conflict, love blooms in the heat of battle.

programme.title: Assault on Precinct 13
programme.desc: Gritty action fires up this intense crime drama. On New Year's Eve inside a Detroit police station, an officer (Ethan Hawke) must round up a makeshift brigade of cops and criminals when the precinct is besieged by a relentless mob. The film is an effective refashioning of the 1976 film of the same name. Laurence Fishburne, Drea de Matteo, Brian Dennehy, John Leguizamo.

programme.title: Barefoot
programme.desc: In this delightful, feel-good romance, a wealthy playboy falls for a sheltered beauty who charms his family at his brother's lavish wedding. Suddenly, the man whose life was going nowhere seems to have found the road to true happiness.

programme.title: Miss Julie
programme.desc: Over the course of a midsummer night in Fermanagh in 1890, an unsettled daughter of the Anglo-Irish aristocracy encourages her father's valet to seduce her.

programme.title: Pitch Perfect
programme.desc: The laughs never stop as a feisty college student gives her school's a cappella group a much-needed makeover by adding some modern hits into the mix during the run-up to a big competition.

programme.title: 10 Years
programme.desc: Adults attend their 10-year high-school reunion in this memorable drama as old flames are rekindled, a repentant bully regresses, rivals compete for the affections of a popular beauty and a musician longs for the crush who inspired his hit single.

programme.title: Unforgettable
programme.desc: In this riveting female-centric thriller, a jilted ex-wife grows jealous of her former husband's new bride, and decides to destroy the latter's reputation in an attempt to get her old life back.

programme.title: Something the Lord Made

programme.title: A Black Lady Sketch Show
programme.sub-title: Sister, May I Call You Oshun?

programme.title: Don't Let Go

It is now up to Jack to talk her through the coming days to save her and her family's lives in this mystery thriller.

programme.title: SI
programme.desc: After a baseball game, an Asian American boy navigates microaggression with his friends through seemingly innocent jokes and games.

programme.title: Downton Abbey

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: While Mundi seeks justice, Amalia and her most trusted advisors make a list of potential enemies; Harriet, Primrose, and the other Orphans attempt to decipher a message; and later, Amalia exposes an unexpected threat.

programme.title: Red Dragon
programme.desc: Anthony Hopkins has his third go-round as Hannibal \"The Cannibal\" Lecter in this chilling 2002 remake of 1986's \"Manhunter.\" This time, the not-so-good doctor shares his expertise with an FBI agent (Edward Norton) who is tracking a serial killer known as \"The Tooth Fairy.\" Ralph Fiennes, Philip Seymour Hoffman, Emily Watson, Harvey Keitel, Frankie Faison.

programme.title: The Mummy Returns
programme.desc: Action and adventure erupt yet again when the evil mummy returns in this effects-laden sequel to the 1999 hit. In 1933, Rick and Evie's son Alex joins the gang to take on the resurrected Imhotep, who's battling the Scorpion King for world domination. Brendan Fraser, Arnold Vosloo, Rachel Weisz, John Hannah, Oded Fehr, Freddie Boath.

programme.title: Precious (?)
programme.desc: This inspirational drama centers on an illiterate, pregnant teen with little hope for the future, until the opportunity to attend an alternative school changes the course of her life.

programme.title: Malice
programme.desc: A murder mystery involving a serial killer targeting female students at a New England college figures into this story about an arrogant surgeon who moves in with a mild-mannered dean and his wife.

programme.title: Serving Sara
programme.desc: Sparkling romantic comedy about a process server sent to deliver divorce papers to the wife of a two-timing cattle baron. When he finally catches up to her, she offers him a million dollars to serve the papers to her philandering husband instead.

programme.title: Cinema Paradiso
programme.desc: A prominent movie director returns to his Sicilian home village for the first time in many years to attend the funeral of the town's former film projectionist, who served as the filmmaker's mentor when he was a young boy.

programme.title: The Scorpion King
programme.desc: An ancient assassin attempts to trounce an evil conqueror by teaming up with a coalition of the remaining \"free tribes\" surviving under tyrannical rule.

programme.title: The Girl With All the Gifts
programme.desc: In this engaging horror thriller set in a world overrun by zombies, a trio of soldiers, a teacher and a scientist are forced to protect a young girl whose immunity to the outbreak could be the key to saving humanity.

programme.title: You Can Count on Me
programme.desc: Oscar nominee Laura Linney and Mark Ruffalo give strong performances in writer-director Kenneth Lonergan's observant study about siblings who renew their bond. Terry (Ruffalo) returns to his sleepy New York home town to borrow money from his sister (Linney), and the reunion sparks conflicting emotions. Matthew Broderick, Jon Tenney, Rory Culkin.

programme.title: The King of Staten Island
programme.desc: Struggling since his father died during his childhood, twenty-something Scott squanders his life on drugs, alcohol, and casual hookups. When his mother brings home a churlish new boyfriend, Scott must face his demons head-on in order to overcome.

programme.title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
programme.sub-title: Last Week Tonight with John Oliver 219
programme.desc: COVID-19 vaccines and vaccine hesitancy; and U.S. government agencies on social media are discussed.

programme.title: Rocky Balboa
programme.desc: Sylvester Stallone wrote, directed and stars in this knockout sixth go-round in the ring cycle, in which the never-say-die Philadelphia palooka comes out of retirement to fight reigning champ Mason \"The Line\" Dixon.

programme.title: Flags of Our Fathers
programme.desc: Clint Eastwood produced, directed and composed the score for this inspiring and engrossing World War II epic. It's the fact-based story of two marines and a sailor (Adam Beach, Jesse Bradford, Ryan Phillippe) who helped raise the flag over Iwo Jima and then were shipped home to help raise money for the war effort. Adapted from the book by Ron Powers and James Bradley, whose father is played by Phillippe. Steven Spielberg is one of the producers. Barry Pepper, Judith Ivey, John Benjamin Hickey.

programme.title: Gone
programme.desc: In this pulse-pounding thriller, a young woman pursues the serial killer who previously abducted her and has now sought vengeance by kidnapping her sister.

programme.title: The Brothers Grimm
programme.desc: In Terry Gilliam's inventive fantasy, the famed authors are cast as con artists who get caught up in a real-life fairy tale involving a haunted forest where girls have been disappearing. Matt Damon and Heath Ledger star in this whimsical adventure. Jonathan Pryce, Monica Bellucci, Peter Stormare, Lena Headey.

programme.title: The Five-Year Engagement
programme.desc: A couple named Tom and Violet find their wedding plans interrupted by a number of surprises over the course of five years in this endearing romantic comedy, as Violet must move to Michigan for school and Tom is frustrated by missed job opportunities.

programme.title: Speed
programme.desc: A bomber has rigged a bus with a bomb and a cop must get on-board while it is traveling to figure out how to get the passengers off.

programme.title: Keeping the Faith
programme.desc: Edward Norton and Ben Stiller are delightful in Norton's directorial debut about a priest and a rabbi who've been friends since childhood. But when another old pal (Jenna Elfman) reunites with the men, one of them is in danger of becoming a third wheel. Eli Wallach, Anne Bancroft, Ron Rifkin, Milos Forman.

programme.title: Desperately Seeking Susan
programme.desc: A bored New Jersey housewife obsessed with the romantic relationship that plays out between two people in the classified ads gets amnesia and believes herself to be the woman in those ads. She hits it off with a handsome young stranger, and is soon being followed by her husband, the real Susan, a mobster looking for jewels stolen from him, and the real Susan's lover.

programme.title: The Cider House Rules
programme.desc: John Irving's Oscar-winning adaptation of his own novel is a poignant drama about a World War II-era orphanage in Maine, where a sensitive lad who grows up under the tutelage of the institute's kindly doctor who performs abortions on the side.

programme.title: Insomnia
programme.desc: Christopher Nolan, of \"Memento\" fame, directed this taut and atmospheric crime thriller, a remake of a 1997 Norwegian film. Al Pacino is in top form as L.A. detective Will Dormer, who travels to a remote Alaska town to investigate a murder. Unable to sleep, the weary Dormer is drawn into an intense cat-and-mouse game with the sly and taunting killer. Robin Williams, Hilary Swank.

programme.title: Rosewater
programme.desc: In this gripping true story, Iranian journalist Maziar Bahari returns to his homeland to report on the 2009 elections, and is taken into custody and tortured by the Revolutionary Guard after submitting footage of civil unrest to the BBC.

programme.title: 27 Dresses
programme.desc: Wedding mania gets a comic spin in the tale of Jane (Katherine Heigl), who's always a bridesmaid and never a bride. Jane's passion for all things nuptial is tested when she's asked to plan her sister's wedding to the man she secretly loves. A cynical columnist (James Marsden) who falls for Jane while surreptitiously writing a human-interest story about her further complicates Jane's dreams of love and marriage.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city buzzes with anticipation over a pending execution, as Penance grapples with a moral calling at odds with Amalia's plan. With the two women at a crossroads, the Orphans must decide whom to follow.

programme.title: Cruel Intentions
programme.desc: The seductive Kathryn (Sarah Michelle Gellar) poses the ultimate challenge to her charming stepbrother, Sebastian (Ryan Phillippe). If he can deflower the headmaster's virgin daughter (Reese Witherspoon), then Sebastian can have Kathryn for one night. If he fails, she gets his vintage car.

programme.title: The High Note
programme.desc: The overworked, overlooked, and underappreciated personal assistant to a superstar singer seizes the opportunity to revitalize her boss's languishing career - and to realize her childhood dream of becoming a music producer. Both women discover friendship and professional fulfillment amidst Los Angeles's competitive music scene.

programme.title: Igby Goes Down
programme.desc: This darkly funny coming-of-age story boasts an outstanding ensemble. Igby is a rich teen who rebels against his dysfunctional family, including a yuppie brother, a tyrannical mother and a mentally ill father.

programme.title: Going in Style
programme.desc: Three elderly friends and retired steelworkers are outraged to learn that their pension fund has been raided by a shady corporation. Soon, they decide to rob one of the corporation's banks to get their money back in this rousing crime comedy.

programme.title: Jersey Girl
programme.desc: Screenwriter-director Kevin Smith (\"Clerks\") ditches his profane stoners for this witty and tender comedy-drama. Ben Affleck stars as a widowed ex-publicist who returns to his humble New Jersey roots to raise his young daughter.

programme.title: Dirty Pretty Things
programme.desc: Gritty, socially conscious thriller about an illegal Nigerian immigrant in London who becomes embroiled with a black-market ring selling human organs.

programme.title: The Rite
programme.desc: Veteran priest Father Lucas (Anthony Hopkins) teaches incredulous seminary student Michael Kovak about performing exorcisms, and together they discover that even the Vatican isn't free from the Devil's influence in this terrifying supernatural thriller. Inspired by a true story.

programme.title: Trick 'r Treat
programme.desc: Your blood will run colder than the chilly fall breeze thanks to this episodic shocker comprised of four interconnected stories set on Halloween night. Anna Paquin stars. Included: a high-school principal moonlights as a serial killer; a college virgin seeks to shed her innocence; a group of teens play a horrific prank; a poor loner gets an unusual visitor.

programme.title: Hours
programme.desc: A New Orleans father must protect his prematurely born daughter in the midst of Hurricane Katrina in this intense tale of survival. As the hospital loses power and patients are evacuated, he faces a series of difficult decisions in an attempt to save her from certain death.

programme.title: The Man in the Iron Mask
programme.desc: The aging Musketeers hatch a plan to overthrow evil King Louis and replace him with his good-natured, tortured twin brother---who has been kept chained and masked in a dungeon. Directed by Randall Wallace, writer of the award-winning film \"Braveheart,\" and loosely based on the novel by Alexander Dumas. Leonardo DiCaprio, Jeremy Irons, John Malkovich, Gerard Depardieu, Gabriel Byrne.

programme.title: Bigger Than the Sky
programme.desc: Marcus Thomas, Amy Smart and John Corbett star in this charming romantic comedy. Thomas plays a sad sack whose life improves when he lands the lead in a community theater production of \"Cyrano de Bergerac,\" then falls for his leading lady. Sean Astin, Clare Higgins. Al Corley directed.

programme.title: The Kitchen
programme.desc: When their mobster husbands are sent to prison by the FBI, three New York housewives decide to continue their husbands' business on their own, soon becoming the most powerful mobsters in 1970s Hell's Kitchen.

programme.title: Magnolia
programme.desc: In this audacious ensemble drama about the intersecting lives of troubled Californians, a dying mogul tries to reunite with his motivational-speaker son, a young quiz-show winner deals with his father's abuse and a drug addict falls for a lonely cop.

programme.title: Talk to Me
programme.desc: Don Cheadle's electrifying portrayal of ex-con Petey Greene, who became an influential, controversial disc jockey in 1960s Washington, D.C., as well as a beloved community activist, cues this charged, fact-based biopic. Cheadle perfectly captures Greene's tell-it-like-it-is bluntness and candor. Chiwetel Ejiofor, Taraji P. Henson, Martin Sheen, Mike Epps. Directed by Kasi Lemmons. Features an excellent period soundtrack that includes James Brown, the Dramatics and Otis Redding.

programme.title: Bounce
programme.desc: Ben Affleck and Gwyneth Paltrow costar in this unusual drama. Affleck plays Buddy, an exec who gives another man his plane ticket as a favor. Minutes after takeoff, the plane crashes. Feeling responsible, Buddy tries to help the man's widow (Paltrow) by entering into a business relationship with her.

programme.title: Ruby Sparks
programme.desc: In this dazzling romantic fantasy, lovelorn novelist Calvin creates a character based on his dream girl and gets the surprise of his life when she turns up in the flesh.

programme.title: Bridget Jones: The Edge of Reason
programme.desc: Renée Zellweger, Colin Firth and Hugh Grant return for this must-see sequel. Charming but insecure Bridget has finally landed the reserved Mr. Darcy (Firth), but she is concerned that their relationship won't last. Adding to her worries is the fact that her new employers have paired her with her womanizing ex-boyfriend, Daniel Cleaver (Grant).

programme.title: Tully
programme.desc: At the encouragement of her brother, Marlo, an overwhelmed mother of three, and her husband Drew hire a young night nurse named Tully to care for their newborn. Tully becomes a confidant for Marlo, who is grappling with her identity as a wife and mother.

programme.title: Good Boys
programme.desc: One day, 12-year-old Max gets invited by the cool kids to a kissing party. Panicked because he doesn't know how to kiss, he enlists the help of two of his friends, Thor and Lucas, to help him uncover the mystery of kissing. After online research proves to be unproductive, they decide to take the drone owned by Max's father in order to spy on the neighboring teens. When the drone unexpectedly crashes, the boys are thrust into an adventure.

programme.title: The Way Back
programme.desc: An alcoholic who has endured family tragedy works to redeem himself by coaching his high school alma mater's basketball team. But as he's brought back to his glory days as a promising athlete, he's forced to confront the demons that derailed him earlier in life.

programme.title: Her Smell
programme.desc: A fading '90s punk rocker struggles with life after the past success of her all-female grunge band. Now playing smaller venues and competing against her own sobriety and the pressures of motherhood, she takes a hiatus from the stage, to find herself and her sober creativity.

programme.title: More American Graffiti
